Items.description:
Ron Francis knocked in Jeff O'Neill's short pass
to the top of the crease 58 seconds into overtime, and the Carolina
Hurricanes stunned the heavily favored Detroit Red Wings 3-2 in
Game 1 of the Stanley Cup finals Tuesday night.

Items.description: The Red Wings, in danger of going down two games to one of the biggest underdogs in finals history, got goals from Nicklas Lidstrom and Kris Draper 13 seconds apart late in the third period to beat the Carolina Hurricanes 3-1 Thursday night.

Items.description:
The oldest player to score a goal -- make
that two goals -- in the Stanley Cup finals ended the third-longest
game in finals history.

the net sometimes scare and frustrate his teammates -- but they've
also led them to one victory from the Stanley Cup.
